INSERT INTO `content` VALUES (1,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Uzzhorod','Uzzhorod',48.62661361694336,22.28849983215332,'Uzzhorod',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0104_.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0206 (2).jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0036.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0353.jpg','village_tourism',NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'Uzhhorod Uzhhorod is most westerly city and also the centre of the Transcarpathia region in Ukraine. It is a city where the Western European and Eastern European civilizations meet. The city is situated on seven hills, on both sides of the river Uzh. ~ The old city\ncentre, built around the river Uzh\nis very nice, with well-preserved\nhistoric buildings. The city is crossed\nby the busy pedestrian zone with\nmany restaurants and patio seating\nareas. The quality of local restaurants\nis nothing to complain about. The\nstreets of the old town lead us to\nthe castle hill, where we find the\nmighty fortress walls of Uzhhorod.\nThe castle now houses the natural\nhistory museum. To the right of the\nentrance gate of the castle, there is an\nopen-air museum of folk architecture\nof Transcarpathia. The museum\nconsists of 28 structures collected from\nall parts of Transcarpathia Ukraine,\nmostly from the mountainous areas\nof the Carpathians. ~ It‘s definitely\nworth trying the local multi-cultural\ncuisine, especially the specialties of\nRuthenians, Hungarians, Romanians\nand Slovaks. The local confectionary\nproducts are also excellent. ~\nUzhhorod forms a gateway to the\nTranscarpathia wine region. Quality\nlocal wines are offered by two main\ntasting rooms. Uzhhorod castle cellar\nis unique. It combines an elegant\ninterior in the style of the Middle Ages,\nand certainly offers the best wines of\nthe Transcarpathia region in addition\nto creating a magical atmosphere\nand interesting “wine tour” through\nTranscarpathia.\n','Ужгород\nУжгород  є  найзахіднішим містом України, а також адміністративним центром Закарпатської області. Це місто в якому переплітаються західноєвропейська та східноєвропейська цивілізації. Місто розташоване на семи пагорбах на обох берегах річки Уж. Старий центр міста, зосереджений навколо річки Уж є надзвичайно гарним з добре збереженими історичними будівлями. Місто перетинає жвава пішохідна зона з великою кількістю ресторанів та зонами відпочинку на терасах. На якість харчування в місцевих ресторанах скаржитись не приходиться. Вулички старого міста приведуть нас на Замкову гору, де ми побачимо могутні стіни Ужгородської фортеці. На сьогоднішній день в замку розташований етнографічний музей. Направо від вхідних воріт замку розташований Музей народної архітектури та побуту Закарпаття. В музеї під відкритим небом знаходиться 28 об’єктів, зібраних з усіх куточків закарпатської частини України, переважно з гірських районів Карпат. Безперечно варто відвідати місцеву мультикультурну кухню, особливо делікатеси русинів, угорців, румунів та словаків.  Чудовими є і кондитерські вироби. Ужгород являється вхідними воротами в закарпатський винний регіон. Якісні місцеві вина вам запропонують, перш за все, в двох дегустаційних залах. Унікальним являється винний погреб Ужгородського замку. Поєднання елегантного інтер’єру в середньовічному стилі та запропоновані, безсумнівно, найкращі вина Закарпатської області, крім чарівної атмосфери, створять цікавий  \"винний тур\" по Закарпаттю.\n\n\n','','Vínna cesta,\nZakarpatská oblasť\nto sú zaujímavé vínne pivnice a degustačné\nmiestnosti.\nUkážky tradičného vinárstva a kultúry\nkonzumácie vína, ktoré sa v Zakarpatskej\noblasti objavili už pred 2000\nrokmi patria k zaujímavým atrakciám.\nPredpokladá sa, že prví vinári\nv oblasti boli Kelti a D áci, ale o rozvoj\nsa zaslúžili aj maďarské kmene, ktoré\npriniesli základné ázijské stolové\ndruhy hrozna. Rozkvet vinohradníctva\na vinárstva nastal 13. storočí,\npo príchode nemeckých a talianskych\nosadníkov, kultivovali vinice\na priniesli nové odrody hrozna.\nZ tohto obdobia sa zachovali vinice\nna okraji Berehova, Vynohradova,\nMukačeva a Užhorodu. Tradícia\nbola neskôr udržiavaná mníchmi\nzo stredovekých kláštorov. Takmer\nvšetky južné svahy sopečných hôr\nod Tokaja (cez Užhorod, Mukačevo,\nSerednye, Berehovo a Vynohradiv)\ndo C hustu boli pokryté vinicami aj\nv období tureckých vpádov, kedy\nboli vytvorené prvé vínne pivnice,\nktoré sa zachovali dodnes. Viac ako\npolovica viníc je sústredená v poľnohospodárskych\npodnikoch. Okrem\nnich na území pôsobí niekoľko stovák\nsúkromných vínnych pivníc a tisíce vinárov.\nStále rastúci záujem o návštevu\nvinohradov a vinárskych závodov\ndáva príležitosť oblasti ponúkať aj\nslužby v cestovnom ruchu ako ubytovanie,\nstravovanie, degustácie a iné\nzážitkové aktivity spojené s kultúrou\nvína. Vo vinárskych oblastiach sa tiež\npravidelne usporadúvajú zaujímavé\nvinárske slávnosti a festivaly.\n','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(2,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Mukachevo','Mukachevo',48.440673828125,22.719806671142578,'Mukachevo',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/2948.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/DSC_0072.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0016.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0799.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1572.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1511.jpg','village_tourism',NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'The town of Mukachevo is one of the most beautiful pearls of the “Silver Land” – Zakarpattya. It has ancient and glorious history. 1118 years have passed since the first note on the town. May 22, 1376 is an important event in Mukachevo’s life. On that date the queen of Hungary and Poland Elizabeth (Erzsébet), who owned the Mukachevo domain, presented the letter on the right for usage of own seal to the town. Therefore, Mukachevo received the status of the town on that day. One of peculiarities of the town is its unique geopolitical and geographical location. The town was a part of different countries during its centuries-old history. It influenced greatly on the architecture of the town and its national-ethnic composition and traditions. Thanks to its centuries-old and multinational history the town became peculiar colorful combination of architectural and cultural peculiarities of different peoples that is evidenced by 19 monuments of architecture and 16 monuments of culture of national importance. That is why it is very interesting and attractive for tourists. \nOne of the most famous tourist attractions and architectural dominant of the town is Mukachevo Castle “Palanok”. It is possible to see it from all points of Mukachevo. Fateful for the town and its citizens events took place here. There are no more than five castles in Europe that are similar to Mukachevo Castle. The chivalrous spirit could be still felt here. Local citizens remember ancient legends and firmly believe that the impregnable fortress will outlive many future generations.\nIt is also worth to visit one of the oldest monasteries in Ukraine, namely the Orthodox Convent of St. Nicholas that stands on the slopes of the Chornecha Mountain and is the biggest one from Zakarpattya holy cloisters,  the Cathedral of St. Martin (the ХІVth century), who is patron of the town, the Gothic Chapel of St. Joseph, monument of architecture of the middle of the XVIIth century  – the White Castle, former residence of Ferenc Rákóczi II, building of the Town Hall of the beginning of the XXth century that is a dominant of quiet central pedestrian historical part of the town, where Mukachevo citizens and guests of the town like to walk, and other ancient monuments.\nThe central square of the town is a traditional place for carrying out of mass events, such as festival “Chervene Vyno” taking place annually in January on the eve of the St. Basil’s Day. The festival’s guests have a possibility to taste and purchase wines made by private wine-makers and famous companies. Besides, “Chervene Vyno” is a real popular festival with Christmas carols and presents.\n','Місто Мукачево є однією з найяскравіших перлин Срібної землі – Закарпаття. Воно має давню і славну історію. Минуло вже 1118 років з часу першої писемної згадки про місто. Знаменною подією в житті Мукачева стало 22 травня 1376 року, адже цього дня королева Угорщини та Польщі Єлизавета (Ержибет), яка володіла Мукачівською домінією, подарувала місту грамоту на право користуватися власною печаткою. Таким чином в цей знаменний день Мукачево отримало статус міста. Також однією з найбільш визначних особливостей міста є його унікальне геополітичне та географічне розташування. За свою багатовікову історію місто неодноразово перебувало у складі різних держав. Це наклало істотний відбиток на архітектуру міста, його національно-етнічний склад та традиції. Завдяки своїй багатовіковій та багатонаціональній історії місто стало своєрідним колоритним поєднанням архітектурних, культурних особливостей різних народів, про що свідчать 19 пам’яток архітектури та 16 пам’яток культури загальнодержавного значення. Саме тому воно є надзвичайно цікавим та привабливим для туристів. \nОднією з найбільш визначних туристичних атракцій  та архітектурною домінантою міста по праву вважають Мукачівський замок «Паланок». Його можна побачити з усіх точок Мукачева. Тут вершилися доленосні для міста і його жителів події. Подібних до Мукачівського замку в Європі залишилося не більше п\'яти. Тут досі витає рицарський дух. Місцеві жителі пам\'ятають старовинні легенди і твердо вірять, що ця неприступна фортеця переживе ще багато поколінь.\nТакож в Мукачеві варто відвідати один з найдавніших в Україні православний Свято-Миколаївський жіночий монастир – найбільший із закарпатських святих обителей, що стоїть з ХІУ ст. на схилах Чернечої гори, кафедральний костел Св. Мартина (ХІV ст.), який є покровителем міста, готичну каплицю Св. Йосипа, пам’ятку архітектури  середини XVII століття – Білий Палац, колишню резиденція Ференца Ракоці ІІ, будівлю міської Ратуші початку ХХ ст., яка є домінантою затишної центральної пішохідної історичної частини міста, в якій дуже полюбляють відпочивати мешканці та гості Мукачева та інші пам\'ятники давнини.\nЦентральна площа міста - традиційне місце проведення масових заходів, в т.ч. фестивалю \"Червене вино”, яке відбувається щороку в січні напередодні дня святого Василя. Гості фестивалю мають змогу продегустувати, а також придбати вина від приватних виноробів та відомих компаній. Окрім того, «Червене вино» — це ще й справжнє народне свято з колядками, щедрівками та подарунками.\n','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(3,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Berehovo','Berehovo',48.20150375366211,22.645681381225586,'Berehovo',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0016.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0566.jpg,img/markerImages/teatralyna.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo_1.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo_3.jpg','village_tourism',NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'Berehove is known especially for the\ncultivation of wine and its thermal\npools. It has a small but beautiful\nhistoric centre, which has a southern,\nRomanian-Hungarian feel. The city\nis considered the capital of the wine\nregion. The best wines are produced by\nthe local enterprises LTD „Berehivske“\nEnterprise „Iceberg“ and Enterprise\n„Cotnari“. Very tasty wines are the\ntypes of Berehivshchyna wines found\nin “Stariy Pidval”, which is more\nthan 300 years old and consists of\n7 interconnected basements. From\nthe north and northeast, the city is\nsurrounded by the volcanic slopes of\nthe Carpathians, which protect the city\nfrom the cold northern winds and they\nform the conditions for the vineyards.\n','Берегово відоме, перш за все,\nвиробництвом доброго вина та\nтермальними басейнами. Місто має\nневеличкий, але гарний історич-\nний центр, який навіює південні\nрумунсько-угорські враження.\nМісто вважається головним містом\nвиноградарства та виноробства у\nрегіоні. Найкращі вина виробля-\nються на місцевих підприємствах\nТО В „Берегівське“, підприємстві\n„Iceberg“ та підприємстві „Cotnari“.\nНадзвичайно смачні сорти Берегів-\nських вин запропонують в „Старому\nпідвалі“, який має понад 300\nроків, і складається з 7 з‘єднаних\nпогребів. З півночі і північного\nсходу місто оточене вулканічними\nсхилами Карпат, які захищають\nмісто від холодних північних вітрів\nі створюють сприятливі умови для\nвиноградників.\n','','Berehovo známe predovšetkým pestovaním dobrého vína a termálnymi bazénmi. Má neveľké, ale krásne historické centrum, ktoré pôsobí južanským rumunsko-maďarským dojmom. Mesto je považované za hlavné mesto vinohradníctva a vinárstva v regióne. Najlepšie vína sa vyrábajú v miestnych podnikoch LTD \"Berehivske\", Enterprise \"Iceberg\" a Enterprise \"Cotnari\". Veľmi chutné vína sú druhy Berehivshchyna vín v \" Stariy Pidval\", ktorá je viac ako 300 rokov a skladá sa zo 7 prepojených pivníc. Zo severu a severovýchodu je mesto obklopené svahmi vulkanických Karpát, ktoré chránia mesto od chladných severných vetrov a tvoria podklad pokrytý vinicami.','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(4,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Uzzhorod','Uzzhorod',48.623199462890625,22.299541473388672,'Tasting room Shardone',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/DSC_0095.jpg,img/markerImages/DSC_0116.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg','vine_bunker',NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'Shardone is the first Uzhhorod tasting room. It has been selected due to following reasons: \n- is one of the most popular and the most attended tourist objects in Uzhhorod; \n- has very convenient location: in ancient part of the town, in pedestrian zone; and\n- is a standard of wine-making traditions and cultivated taste. \nIt is said in legends that representatives of Uzhhorod noble families gathered in that cellar together and discussed different issues with foreign ambassadors when drinking good wines. \n','Шардоне - перший ужгородський дегустаційний зал. Обраний з кількох причин: \n- є одним із найпопулярніших і найбільш відвідуваних туристичних об’єктів Ужгорода; \n- має надзвичайно вдале розташування: у старовинній частині міста, в пішохідній туристичній зоні; \n- є еталоном виноробних традицій та вишуканого смаку. \nЛегенди твердять, що саме в цьому підвалі у давні часи збиралися ужгородські вельможі і за келихом доброго вина вели дружні бесіди із заморськими послами. \n________________________________________\n','','Šardone – prvá užhorodská degustačná sála. Vybraná z niekoľkých dôvodov: \n- je jedným z najpopulárnejších a najnavštevovanejších turistických objektov v Užhorode; \n- má veľmi dobrú polohu: v historickej časti mesta, v pešej turistickej zóne; \n- je etalónom vinárskych tradícií a vycibreného vkusu. \nLegendy hovoria, že práve v tejto pivnici sa za dávnych čias schádzali užhorodskí  šľachtici a za pohárom dobrého vína priateľsky besedovali so zahraničnými veľvyslancami. \n________________________________________\n','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(5,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Uzzhorod','Seredne',48.322818756103516,22.3098856,'State enterprise Agro-industrial firm âLeankaâ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/DSC_0102.jpg,img/markerImages/7245.jpg,img/markerImages/2641.jpg,img/markerImages/2948.jpg,img/markerImages/3033.jpg','vine_bunker',NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'It is one of few remained post-Soviet Union agro-industrial enterprises specialized in wine-making.  It is a high-capacity enterprise located in 5 settlements. The name of enterprise is „Leanka“ that means a „girl“,  if to translate from Hungarian language.  „Leanka“ is a sort of grapes that is being used in production of wine „Serednyanske“ for 60 years. \nWine cellars of agro-industrial firm „Leanka“ are a valuable monument of architecture of the XVIth century and considered ones of the best in Europe. \nIs irreplaceable and one of the most interesting objects of Zakarpattya wine route.  \n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(6,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Uzzhorod','Seredne',48.53893280029297,22.49751853942871,'Serednye Castle',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0799.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1572.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1511.jpg','ruins',NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'Serednye castle was typical defensive structure for Western Europe of twelfth century and had a look of tower donjon. These towers were not intended for extended stay. If needed, they could become a powerful defensive point, because the area had a good view of it and could lead circular firing. In addition, these towers had a circular system of walls and ditches. The Serednye Castle had all these components. \nClose to \"door\" in the floor \"east\" part of building is seen a pit covered with stones. Probably there was a draw well.\nIn the Middle Ages, the Templars received the right to trade with Solotvynska salt. The \"Salt Road\" from Pidcarpathian mines to Europe passed through Transcarpathia. The Templars quickly built series of fortifications along the salt road that were used as customs points, and in case - as points of dislocation of small garrisons that guarded the salt road. According to legend, the Serednye castle was constructed by monks of the Templers Order in XII century.\n New researches, excavations and measurements give reason to state that a square central tower that is visible above the surface of the earth is only a part of this unique castle that stands on the plain. The area around the castle is about three acres. These are ditches, ramparts, walls ...\nCastle building was protected by four defensive lines. Numerous findings in the castle dated by 15-16th centuries. Serednye castle just began to discover its secrets.\n\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(7,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Uzzhorod','Nevytske',48.6810188293457,22.409317016601562,'Nevytskyi Castle ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0104_.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0206 (2).jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0036.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0353.jpg','castle',NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'The first mention of the village refers to 1427 year. In letters and other written sources known as \"Nyuiske\", \"Newicke\", \"Newiczke\", and located 12 km north from Uzhhorod. The village is known by the same name of the castle, which is actually located in the neighboring village of Kamyanitsya.\nIn the northern part of the village a cremation with burial grounds are discovered in the 70\'s of last century. Human remains were found in clay urns. Burial mound dated of VI - V century before Christ era.\nThe first documented mention about the castle dated of XIV century, according to other sources -  1248 year. Then it was a wooden outpost, owned by Obo Omodey, one of the rebels, who seen the Hungarian King Charles Robert Anjourskyi as an alien and protégé of the Pope. After the Battle under Rozhony in 1312, army leaded by Omodey was defeated, and Nevytske was taken by Peter Petenko (Petunya). Soon Petenko raised new uprising against the king. Transcarpathia asked for help from the nearby Galician prince, but exhausted by Tatars Galician Rus could not help the rebels. In 1321 the royal forces captured the last bulwark of the rebels - Nevytsky castle.\nIn 1328 Drugets family got the castle and rebuilt it. So there was a stone fortress surrounded by a moat. In terms – it is a wrong ellipse with patios of 35 to 12 meters. There is a spring source in the yard remains in diameter of 3.5 meters.\nThe castle had four towers and residential buildings. On the part of Uzh river, where castle’s mountain is breaking, the hillside is reinforced by supported walls.\nIn 1644 the castle was partially destroyed by the troops of Rákóczi II. Since than the castle has not been rebuilt.\nFrom the observation deck on the tower a nice view for dam of Uzh river and neighboring villages are opening. In clear weather here you can see a whole suburb of Uzhhorod. \n \n\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(8,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Mukachevo','Mukachevo',48.45577621459961,22.755388259887695,'Medoviy Dim',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0016.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0566.jpg,img/markerImages/teatralyna.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo_1.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo_3.jpg','tasting_hall',NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'The object is original and peculiar one. It is the part of „Honey tourist route of Zakarpattya“ that is being initiated in the region. It is the first house of honey in Zakarpattya that offers tasting of honey and honey drinks. ','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(9,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Mukachevo','Mukachevo',48.45663070678711,22.701379776000977,'Keltskiy Dvir pid Lovachkoyu',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/DSC_0102.jpg,img/markerImages/7245.jpg,img/markerImages/2641.jpg,img/markerImages/2948.jpg,img/markerImages/3033.jpg','tasting_hall',NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'It is situated on the route. It is peculiar because of the fact that it is located in the ancient cellar at the foot of Mountain Lovachka. Vine has been grown on the territory of agricultural guest house   „Keltskiy Dvir pid Lovachkoyu“ since the IVth century . The locality is a historical one because ancient Keltic settlement “opium”, is located nearby. The tasting cellar offers to the guests unique Zakarpattya sorts of fruit liqueurs and tinctures as well as several sorts of vermouth made from three dozens of herbs.  The following liqueurs are proposed for tasting: chereshnivka (made from cherries), dychkivka (wild pears), khurmivka (persimmons), skoroshivka, persykova (peaches) and well-known Zakarpattya slyvovytsya (plum brandy); tinctures: kedrivka (cedar), yaphynivka (blueberries), brusnychna (cowberries) and zhuravlyna (cranberries). Snacks – salted cucumbers and tomatoes, sandwiches with homemade salted beef and lard. Price of tasting – up to 50 UAH/person. \nTasting is accompanied with a presentation on wine-making and peculiarities of the locality where tasting cellar is situated.\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(10,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Mukachevo','Mukachevo',48.43174743652344,22.687265396118164,'Palanok Castle',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0799.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1572.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1511.jpg','castle',NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'The main interest for visitors to enjoy is the medieval fortress, Palanok castle. It rises almost 70 metres above the surrounding countryside on a hill of volcanic origin. It contains a unique tasting room.  ','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(11,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Mukachevo','Bobovyshe',48.52788162231445,22.670509338378906,'Bobovyshche',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0104_.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0206 (2).jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0036.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0353.jpg','vine_bunker',NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'Village Bobovyshche is situated at 15 kilometers’ distance from Mukachevo near mountains Kychera and Dubova. The village is famous for its wine-makers far beyond Mukachevo district. The village was established in the beginning of the ІVth century. There live 2 thou. people. Private wine-makers work here. Their wine is famous among real experts on “sun” drinks. Bobovyshche wines are considered as a business-card of the region. The wines are more aromatic than some of the French wines and are second to none of Odessa and Crimean wines thanks to richer microelements of soils.\nThe village is popular for its wine cellars that are in disposal of enterprise “Bobovyshche”. The total capacity of Bobovyshche cellar is more than a million liters of wine. Its circle length is one kilometer. The cellars are dug in the mountain. The soil layer of 50 m is above the cellars. The chestnut forest is planted above. Wines of enterprise “Bobovyshche” repeatedly participated in different specialized competitions and were granted with letters of commendations and other awards. \nThe wines are made applying old recipes and traditional technologies. They ripen in oak barrels. Specialists consider that oak, the barrels are made from, gives to wine peculiar piquancy and aroma. \nApart from traditional for Zakarpattya wine “Isabella”, the factory produces vintage wines, such as “Saperavi”, “Merlot”, “Cabernet”, “Cabernet Oksamyt” and “Leanka”. The real proud of the enterprise in that nomination is “Starovynniy Zamok”. As regards dessert wines – “Sontse v Bokali”, “Izabella Desertna”, “Cahors” and, certainly, dainty “Troyanda Zakarpattya” made from the harvest of 1986.\nThe tasting room is situated in the mountain. Both dry and dessert wines are proposed for tasting. They are to the taste of different people.\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(12,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Mukachevo','Bobovyshe',48.52784729003906,22.670652389526367,'Private wine-maker Vasyl Antalovskiy',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0016.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0566.jpg,img/markerImages/teatralyna.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo_1.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo_3.jpg','vine_bunker',NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'Tasting cellar in village Bobovyshche,private object. It has been selected as an alternative to factory cellars of the state ownership form of agro-industrial commercial enterprise „Bobovyshche“ that is located nearby.   It is located in traditional Zakarpattya wine-making district – Mukachevo district. The cellar’s owner is a member of the Association of private wine-growers and private wine-makers of Zakarpattya. \n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(13,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Mukachevo','Chinadievo',48.484779357910156,22.831268310546875,'Chinadievo Castle',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/2948.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/DSC_0072.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0016.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0799.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1572.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1511.jpg','castle',NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'At the distance of 12 kilometers on the east from Mukachevo, where the mountains are too close to the river Latorytsya, is located the village Chynadiyevo. Its history is closely connected with the history of Mukachevo. In written sources village Chynadievo is first mentioned in 1214 as Saint Mikolos. This Hungarian name appears in official documents until 1944 and comes from built here and named after St. Nicholas feudal estate. In 1264 King Ishtvan V presented village Chynadiyeovo to Master Aladar, the royal representative to the Prince of Galician. At the end of XIV century, in 1387 Chynadiyevo dominion goes into possession of magnate Baron Pereni. In XV century in the village was build a castle, which belonged to the owner of dominion. The castle is preserved till present. It\'s designed like the older Romanesque feudal strongholds.\nOutside the castle is like a fortress - a solid gray two-storey building with two three-tier corner towers, a wall thickness of 1 m. The castle has the form of improper quadrangle stretched from north to south. From the top the building resembles the letter \"П\", broad, with short sides. The first floor of the palace - six rooms and a hall that once was called the chamber with the spacious lobby. The second floor according to its plan somehow repeats the first - there are also six rooms, a bit smaller, and a large hall. The castle’s rooms are blocked spherical down from striking, while the towers are with cross vault. From the first floor to the second led wooden stairs that were inside the castle at the center part of the building. Since the foundation of the feudal household were farmers’ natural duties, in the castle were large cellars for storing food and grain. \nAlmost the whole building is covered by saddle roof, just south-east and north-west wing – three-ply, and in the towers - hip roof. Under the roof extends a series of small windows, loopholes, which seems to surround the entire building. When Dominion was handed out to a new owner, the owner of the castle was changed as well. In 1574 Chynadievo Dominion was bought by Mykhaylo Teleghdi for 22 thousand forints. In 1610 the castle was bought by Ishtwan N’yari. With appropriate request he asked the king, informing that he was ready to pay 7000 HUF. But he had to wait entire 15 years. In a period of 15 years a court of arm appeared under the castle doors, but this court of arms belonged to family Lon’yoi. In 1657 the castle was considerably damaged by Polish troops of Prince Lubomirski, which forced its owners to make a reconstruction work. But over time, the castle gradually lost its strategic importance. At the beginning of XVIII century the construction ceased meets its original purpose. However, during an anti Habsburg War 1703-1711, the castle has served for the rebels - here the leader of the movement retreated Prince Ferenc II R?k?czi revolt after the defeat of Austrian troops under Mukachevo on June 27, 1703.\nAfter the finishing of the last anti Habsburg War Mukachevo-Chynadievo Dominion (in 1612 as result of the consolidation of Mukachevo and Chynadievo dominions was created one new Mukacheov-Chynadievo dominion) went into possession of the Austrian Emperor. In 1726 Emperor Charles VI presented Mukachevo-Chynadievo dominion, together with the village Chynadievo, to Archbishop Count Schonborn, whose family owned Chynadievo almost two centuries.\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(14,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Berehovo','Kidyosh',48.21809768676758,22.69736099243164,'Kidyosh',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0799.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1572.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1511.jpg','vine_bunker',NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'Kidyosh is the village in Berehovo district of Zakarpatska oblast. It is located in picturesque locality at the foot of volcanic mountains. The settlement and bronze subjects of the end of 2 thou. B.C. have been found in the village.\nIt is said that the rewash the skete on the place of the village. Hungarian king Salamon (the years of rule 1063 – 1074), who was the son of king Andras (Endre) I and Anastasiya Yaroslavna, daughter of Kyiv prince Yaroslav Mudriy, spent the last years of his life there. The king decided in such a way to atone for his sin of the blood of battles by prayer.\nAccording to one data the village was established at the end of the 12th century and according to the other – in 1322. It was named Kuyosh and Zmiyivka.\nThe village lands we reowned by Hungarian kings and properfeud al lords and at the end of the 19th century – the family of prince Karoli.\nDuring all the history the forests surrounding the village we reused as the place for rest of Hungarian kings and were considered asking’s estate. That territory was owned by the family of prince Karoli in the middle of the 1800s.\nLocal citizens have preserved agricultural traditions. 50 hectares of European sort vineyards are preserved. They are situated in the tract of mountain Visszatekinte (that means in Hungarian language – the one that turns back to look at something), where work 42 private wine-makers.\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(15,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Berehovo','Kidyosh',48.22269821166992,22.69060707092285,'Wine cellar of Shoshsâ family',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/DSC_0102.jpg,img/markerImages/7245.jpg,img/markerImages/2641.jpg,img/markerImages/2948.jpg,img/markerImages/3033.jpg','vine_bunker',NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'It is the part of Zakarpattya wine route. The object is located in traditional wine-making district – Berehovo district with considerable part of Hungarian population and traditions.  The owner Karlo Shosh is a wine-maker in the third generation. He produces wine from 60 sorts of grapes that are personally grown on own 6 ha of vineyards.  Assortment of personally made production is wider in comparison with other wine-makers of Berehovo or other wine-making districts of Zakarpattya. ','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(16,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Berehovo','Bene',48.16765213012695,22.761444091796875,'Paraska wine-cellar',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg','vine_bunker',NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'The village is famous for vineyards and delicate wines of wine-maker Yuriy Paraska. Yuriy considers himself more a viticulturist, than a wine-maker. He collects not bottles with wine, but sorts of grapes. He dreams to restore European sorts of grapes, particularly forgotten Linner selections. Additionally, Yuriy Paraska can propose for tasting 30 sorts of wine, starting from brand “Kadarka”, during the tasting. ','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(17,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Berehovo','Velyki Berehy',48.2330207824707,22.74928855895996,'Velyki Berehy',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/DSC_0095.jpg,img/markerImages/DSC_0116.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg','village_tourism',NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'The village was established in 1214. The population is 2.5 thou. people. The village was known as the small settlement in Bereg comitat from the XIVth century. The oldest known seal with the coat of arms of the Beregs (picture of the bull’s head) is dated 1567. It was the small town of Nadtysyanskiy povit of Bereg comitat in the XIXth century. In historical context the village is famous for development of viticulture of Hungary and other countries. \nThe building of the palace of the Beregs family is worth to visit. It was built approximately in 1905 and is situated in the main street in the direction to the lakes. Hungarian Humanitarian and Natural History Lyceum financed by the Reformatory Church is located there now.\nTwo lakes with equipped zone for recreation and fishing are located outside the village, The Museum of Weaving with demonstration of the process and different goods functions under the local school.\nThousands of grapes bushes of different sorts are grown on the territory of the village. Such sorts as Muller-Thurgau, Isabella, Riesling, Holubok and other are grown here. Local citizens are also proud of such wines as Saperavi, Cahors and Chorniy Doctor. ','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(18,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Berehovo','Velyki Berehy',48.235450744628906,22.755535125732422,'Private wine-maker Ivan Ursta',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/DSC_0095.jpg,img/markerImages/DSC_0116.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg','vine_bunker',NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'It is a private object. Its originality is formed by aromatic wines and personality of the owner, who is of Hungarian nationality, knows wine-making well and takes a great interest in selection. It is located in traditional wine-making district of Zakarpattya – Berehovo district. The object has convenient location: near central motor road and between towns Berehovo and Irshava. Private wine-maker Ursta I.I. proposes tasting of 7 elite wines that is accompanied by the story on development of local viticulture and wine-making from the times of the Roman Empire in his own wine cellars.','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(19,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Berehovo','Yanoshi',48.252376556396484,22.626733779907227,'Yanoshi',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0016.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0566.jpg,img/markerImages/teatralyna.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo_1.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo_3.jpg','village_tourism',NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'Yanoshi is the last village before Berehovo, if you come here from Mukachevo. Its population is 2 thou. people. The village is known from 1321 and from 1364 as a property of queen Erzsébet. The Slavs called Yanoshi “Ivanoshi” or simply “Ivanivka” (during 1921-1939, Yanoshi – 1484 and Ivanoshi – 1321 according to documents). The village was devastated by the Tatars in 1566.\nThe Greek Catholic Church of the Patronage of the Mother of God (1834, repairs – 1924 and 1976) is situated in Yanoshi. The local parish of the Greek Catholic Church was established in 1743 (wooden church-predecessor was established in 1748).\nWine-growers and wine-makers of Berehivshchyna established a union in the form of Wine Order of St.Ventsel in 2002. The Order consists of about 30 participants from all Zakarpattya, who help to preserve and restore the best traditions of Zakarpattya wine-making and viticulture thanks to their enthusiasm and work. ','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(20,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Berehovo','Yanoshi',48.252376556396484,22.626733779907227,'House of Wine âBeregvidekâ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/DSC_0095.jpg,img/markerImages/DSC_0116.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg','tasting_hall',NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'It is simultaneously a kind of museum: here is an ancient press for grapes pressing and other wine-making tools as well as ordinary and large bottles with alcoholised grapes. The bar is decorated with photos demonstrating the process of grapes processing into the wine. Wine samples rewarded with festival awards are proposed for tasting. Tasting samples are selected by visitors as usual.  Dry white wines “Muscat”, “Leanka”, “Muller Thurgau” and “Frantsuska Desyatka” of wine factory “Chizay”, semi sweet wine “Korolivska Leanka” and so on. ','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(21,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Berehovo','Berehovo',48.2028694152832,22.655179977416992,'Stariy Pidval',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0799.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1572.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1511.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'It is a part of Zakarpattya wine route. It is the ancient cellar that is about 300 years old. People say that it has been dug by the captured Turks. Owners independently grow grapes and produce own wine according to traditional technologies. ','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(22,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Uzzhorod','Goriany',48.606231689453125,22.336931228637695,'Gorianska Rotonda',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/DSC_0102.jpg,img/markerImages/7245.jpg,img/markerImages/2641.jpg,img/markerImages/2948.jpg,img/markerImages/3033.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'Gorianska rotonda stands on a rocky ledge of Antalovetska meadow found in suburb of Uzhhorod. It has spectacular views of the forests and the Carpathian Mountains.\nThis is the most valuable and oldest monument of churche architecture that remains in Ukraine since twelfth century and has secondary importance after Sophia Kyievska. Only three buildings of this type remain accross Europe. Two of them are in the Hungarian towns of Korca and Kishzombor.\nAmazing murals impress visitors by its qualitative performance, and at the same time by its simplicity and vitality of the characters. Today, scientists believe that the frescoes in Horiany represent the early Renaissance era and were performed by unsurpassed Italian masters of Giotto school in the XIV century. \nThe walls of the temple depict scenes from the New Testament. Main topics are: \"The Annunciation\", \"Escape to Egypt\", \"Passion\", \"Gifts of the Magi\", \"Christmas\", \"Resurrection.\" Interestingly, in the center of these scenes always a woman presented – a happy mother, a suffering mother, a young bride.\n   Gorianska rotonda has a hexagon shape (rectangular nave was built later). In this regard there is an interesting legend exists about the temple that can cleanse from evil spirits and demonic forces, and to give person possibility to touch the eternity. It is based on the fact that heksohram or the hexagon is the ancient astral character.\nMasters, who built such buildings in the old ages, believed that the hexagon symbolizes supernatural power of the sun and light, immortality and eternity. People believed that when someone walks into a hexagon than dark forces are gone.\n\n\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(23,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Uzzhorod','Uzzhorod',48.62166976928711,22.306751251220703,'Uzhhorod Castle',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0016.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0566.jpg,img/markerImages/teatralyna.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo_1.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo_3.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'References to the Uzhhorod castle have found in ancient documents and chronicles.\nThe Uzhhorod castle is one of the fortress on borders of the Kiev State, characterized by the same features as the other fortifications of ancient Ukrainian-Russian state, particularly in the Carpathians. Here, for example, walls, towers, gates and bridges were built of wood. The line of defense of the fortress consisted of: earth mound width of 10-12 m and height of 7.8 m, in front a ditch was dug of 5-6 meters depth. The wooden fence completed the land mound (\"Grazhda\").\nAbout the strength of the castle says that fact that in 1086 Cuman hordes led by Khan Kuteskom could not posses it ... The castle was fiercely defended by defenders during Golden Horde invasion in the spring of 1241, and were unable to resist the Horde - hail and other buildings of the city were destroyed.\nThe further destiny of the castle is closely linked with the history of Uzhhorod. In the early fourteenth century it belonged to Peter Petenko who was the enemy of Hungarian King Charles Robert. After suppression a rebellion in year of 1317 led by Petenko, in the year of 1322 the castle was passed to Druhets family which is actually an Italian aristocratic family of French origin, that owned the castle to 90th of XVII century, that means more than 360 years.\nIn 1692 the castle became the property of earl Nikolai Bercheni who is the husband of Christina Druget. Nicholas Bercheni was a colleague and a friend of Ferenc Rákóczi II that was a head of the national liberation war of Hungarians against the Habsburgs in years of 1703-1711. Nikolai Bercheni did much for Uzhgorod to boost its cultural life.\nIn year of 1775, at the request of Bishop Andrey Bachynskyi, the Austrian Empress Maria Theresa passed the castle to Mukachevo Greek Catholic diocese, than since 1780 a theological seminary was placed within the castle. It extited there until 1945.\nThe palace has over 40 rooms. The biggest once, the knight hall, located on the second floor, where celebrations, receptions took place.\nThe castle chapel is what attracts an attention, especially the ceiling which is painted on religious manner by the famous academic painter Ferdinand Vydra in 1857.\nCurrently within the castle the Transcarpathian museum, wine tasting hall, restaurant are located. Here sometimes knights’ tournaments are held.\n\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(24,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Uzzhorod','Uzzhorod',48.62013626098633,22.307193756103516,'Museum of folk architecture and life in Uzhhorod',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/DSC_0102.jpg,img/markerImages/7245.jpg,img/markerImages/2641.jpg,img/markerImages/2948.jpg,img/markerImages/3033.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'Museum of folk architecture and life is an open-air museum in Uzhgorod has being  established in 1965. Skansen is located near Uzhgorod castle and consists of architectural monuments of ancient Transcarpathian village and samples of oldest and most wider types of folk art.\nThe whole space of the museum is 5.5 hectares. Here are represented houses of  Transcarpathians  of low-lying areas (Dolinians, Romanians and Hungarians) and Highlanders (Boyko and Hutsul). In the open-air museum 7 guest houses, 6 houses, a bell, a school, smithy, mill, pot-house are located. The museum has over 14,000 exhibits. For a particular attention, a church deserves that come from Shelestovo village of Mukachevo district (year of 1777) - one of two authentic Lemko churches that has been preserved in the territory of Ukraine. The temple is a sample of classic combination of two styles of folk architecture - Boyko and barolovoho.\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(25,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Uzzhorod','Uzzhorod',48.55921936035156,22.38103675842285,'Ploteni palace ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/DSC_0095.jpg,img/markerImages/DSC_0116.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'The village of Velyki Lazy is a hometown of a famous composer and one of the best violinists of Europe of 19th century Nandor (Ferdinand) Ploteni (1844-1933).\n He was the first violinist of Hungarian National Opera; at the most prestigious world’s stages he performed with brilliant composers Franz Liszt and Johannes Brahms, with the famous scientific F. List Toman István and Hungarian violinist Ede Remeni.\nIn 1870 Ploteni received the title of count, than reached the top of world glory returned back to the Velyki Lazy in 1896,  where built a palace and found a  park.\nThe palace hosted the best intellectuals of Transcarpathia, there artistic performances were hold, social and political developments in Europe were discussed.\nAfter World War II Ploteni properties passed to the Soviet government. Count vineyards and cellars were the basis for brandy factory establishment, and the palace turned into extracurricular educational institution. Nowadays the building of the palace is used as Uzhgorod district center of children\'s art, and in summer is used as a children\'s recreation center.\n   A memorial plaque of Ploteni and F. Liszt are settled on the building of the former palace. \n\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(26,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Uzzhorod','Palad-Komarivtsi',48.526702880859375,22.175695419311523,'Reformative church in Palad-Komarivtsi ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/2948.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/DSC_0072.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0016.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0799.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1572.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1511.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'Two villages - Palad and Komarivtsi in year of 1943 was united into one under name of Palad-Komarivtsi village. \nIn year of 1462, the church is mentioned under name of St. Michael, that was placed in front of Michael Palad house.\nThe church stands on a hill in the center of the village. Extraordinary value murals have discovered in 2006.\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(27,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Berehovo','Bene',48.16761016845703,22.761117935180664,'Bene',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0016.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0566.jpg,img/markerImages/teatralyna.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo_1.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo_3.jpg','vine_bunker',NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'Village Bene is situated in the eastern part of Zakarpatska oblast near Ukrainian-Hungarian border in Berehovo district. It is located on the right bank of the river Borzhava and is 5 km remote from the river Tysa, 12 km – from district centre Berehovo, 80 km – from oblast centre Uzhhorod and is situated 112 meters above sea level.  Lviv railway is at the outskirts of the village. \nAs opposed to the most of settlements the name of village Bene remained the same during many centuries.\nThe first written note on the village is dated 1269 in granting letter of King Bela IV. It is the smallest village located on the wine route both in Berehivshchyna and Zakarpattya.\nWarm climate and hilly locality provide the local population with excellent possibility to be engaged in viticulture. Local citizens call the present district “Kish Tokaj” (“Small Tokaj”). It is possible to taste inimitable taste of the most famous wines, such as brand Kadarka, Muscat Ottonel, Traminer, Riesling Italian, Muscat Poloskej, Furmint Samorodniy, Muscat Yellow, Phetyaska, Leanka and two dozens of other sorts.\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(28,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Berehovo','Berehovo',48.205650329589844,22.648250579833984,'Wine Museum',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0104_.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0206 (2).jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0036.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0353.jpg','museums',NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'It is the part of Zakarpattya wine route. The object is located in traditional wine-making district – Berehovo district with considerable part of Hungarian population and traditions.  ','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(29,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Uzzhorod','Uzzhorod',48.62149429321289,22.306472778320312,'Tasting room in the cellars of Uzhhorod',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/DSC_0102.jpg,img/markerImages/7245.jpg,img/markerImages/2641.jpg,img/markerImages/2948.jpg,img/markerImages/3033.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'It is peculiar because of its location in the Uzhhorod Castle that is the most ancient one in Ukraine and is more than 1000 years old.  \n6 best samples of Zakarpattya wines are proposed for degustation – 3 white and 3 red ones. Tasting is accompanied with a presentation on wine-making.\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(30,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Mukachevo','Mukachevo',48.43141174316406,22.68733024597168,'Tasting cellar of Mukachevo castle âPalanokâ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0016.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0566.jpg,img/markerImages/teatralyna.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo_1.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo_3.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'It is a peculiar one because it is situated in Mukachevo Castle “Palanok” that is a remarkable military and architectural monument of the Middle Ages.\nWines of trade mark “Chizay” (wine-making company Joint Enterprise “Iceberg”, Berehovo). The offer is the following: Cabernet (dry red), Sauvignon (dry white), Tamyanka (white semi sweet), Muscat (semi sweet), Izabella Zakarpatska (rose wine), Rubin Zakarpattya (red semi sweet), Sontse v Bokali (white dessert), Cahors (red dessert), Bila Slyva (fruit wine) and Vyshnya (fruit wine).\nThere are 10 positions + snack for every participant separately.\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(31,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Perecynskiy','Zarichovo',48.77014923095703,22.515060424804688,'Ðthnographic museum Â«LEMKYVSKA SADYBAÂ»',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0104_.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0206 (2).jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0036.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0353.jpg','museums',NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'The museum is placed in one of authenticity Lemko house 1902 year’, that located in Zarichovo village in single hill, where landscape of Uzhanska valley is viewed. The house is built in 1902 year from beech blocks. Here, the interior is a typical Lemko home early XX century. The complex of buildings includes: housing part (cabin, porch and pantry) and utility room (barn, shed and small shed) located in the same row, under the common roof. This is the type of construction that typical for ethnographic group of Lemko. The house is collected by traditional daily stuffs that reflect the material culture of Lemko: the porch - a wooden mortar, millstones, large wooden bowls, tubs for cabbage with straw cover in the barn - vintage joiner’s tools, wooden barrels, crockery, boots in the room - table, carved bed, a wardrobe, a wooden cradle that made by hands of the owner.  \nSpiritual Lemko culture preserves and reproduces the folklore-ethnographic ensemble \"Lemkivchanka.\" The museum complex was established in 1985.\nVisitors will be treated with traditional dishes of Lemko cuisine and Lemko miracle drink (herbal tea with seven herbs gathered on Friday at dawn on the eve of \"Green fests\" in the local mountains).\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(32,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Perecynskiy','Likitsary',48.77705764770508,22.722429275512695,'Wooden church of St. Vasiliy the Great',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0799.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1572.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1511.jpg','visual',NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'Gable roof leaning on wooden column reveals the way to the church of St. Basil the Great, which is the only wooden churche in Perechynsky district of Transcarpathia. A kind of church is the backdrop for an array of magnificent mountain valley Rivna. The temple was built of pine tree in the XVII century. Originally the church had three hills, which corresponded to Boykivska style. During reconstruction in 1748, it acquired a modern look. Near the church there is a wooden framed belfry with two bells. \nWe can note that the site chosen for the church masters equipped at a high slope, making it possible to feel his dominance over the surrounding landscape. According to Michael Syrokhman, sometimes these paintings resemble perfectly calibrated theatrical scenery.\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(33,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Perecynskiy','Lumshory',48.80005645751953,22.713855743408203,'Lumshory village',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/DSC_0095.jpg,img/markerImages/DSC_0116.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg','wellness',NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'Curative specifics of hydrogen sulfide mineral water furthest mountain corner of Perechyn of Lumshory village long time ago have been noticed by locals. Everyone is offered to swim in vat of mineral water. Tourists need to get into the 1000-liter capacity, under which a fire is burning. The water is heated to +40-45 ° C. These baths enhance the activity of the musculoskeletal and the nervous system.\nThe first hydro hospital is built here in 1600 year. Cold mineral water people poured into wooden troughs, and there threw hot stones from fire. After that, they jumped into the water. When in the neighboring village of Turya Remeta a factory was built, there cast two 250-liter iron tubs. They heated mineral water and poured to the troughs.\nAfter First World War both vats lost. In 1970, a local resident Vladimir Ap\'yari dug up one of them in the woods near the stream, the other is now in the Vienna Museum.\nTourist attraction lies in the fact that the recovery procedure is going on outdoor regardless of the season.\nOnce you are well sweat in hot water, it is advised to jump into the cold river water. An hour later, the contrast procedure is useful to repeat 3-4 times. Especially, in winter when the temperature drops to -10 ° C. The recovery from sciatica, rheumatism, osteochondrosis diseases are high. \n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(34,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Velykiy Berezniy','Velykiy Berezniy',48.893638610839844,22.457679748535156,'Uzhanskiy National Nature Park',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,' Uzhanskiy National Nature Park in the framework of the Ukrainian Carpathians was established in September of 1999 on the basis of nature reservation objects existing in the upper reaches of the river Uzh in the beginning of the ХХth century. Particularly, reserves “Stuzhytsya” and “Tykhiy”, named after the closest settlements Stuzhytsya and Tykhiy, were established at the Austrian-Hungarian times in 1908 aimed at preserving virgin forests.\n   During its short history the park became the member of the Federation of Nature and National Parks of Europe “Europark\" and was included in the list of UNESCO World Natural Heritage “The Primeval Beech Forests of the Carpathians” in July of 2007.\n   The Uzhanskiy National Nature Park is a unique natural treasure of the world scale that includes rare combination of wild nature and richness of cultural heritage. It is a part of the unique in the world trilateral International Biosphere Reserve “The Eastern Carpathians” consisting of protected territories of Poland (Bieszczadzki Park Narodowy, regional parks:  Tsisniansko-Vetlinski and the Syan Valley), Slovakia (Národný Park Poloniny”) and Ukraine (Nadsyanskiy Regional Park). The most part of the park’s territory is covered by ethnic lands of the Lemky – small ethnic group of the Ukrainians who have lived in the mountains since the ancient times.\n   The park annually attracts more and more attention  from the side of scientists, nature lovers and tourists from Europe and other parts of the world due to its nature and historical and cultural heritage (karst caves near village Knyahynya, the place of falling down of the biggest in Europe Knyahynya meteorite in tract Chorni Mlaky in 1866,  springs of crystal-clear healing water of “Naphtusya”, “Narzan” and “Yesentuki” types, gigantic trees “Dido-dub” (“Grandfather Oak”) and “Champion” Oak in village Stuzhytsya that are the oldest and the biggest oaks in Ukraine as well as wooden churches of the Boyky and the Lemky styles. Recreation activity is aimed at creating the conditions for tourism development. With such a purpose lots of recreation places are equipped, 17 environmental cognitive routes are developed and number of subjects rendering recreation services is increased. Nature protection actions with pupils of local schools take place on regular basis, ones participate in exhibitions of different levels as well as leaflets, bulletins of environmental cognitive direction, guidelines and booklets are published. \n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(35,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Velykiy Berezniy',NULL,49.08103561401367,22.562650680541992,'Mountain Kremenets',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/2948.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/DSC_0072.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0016.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0799.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1572.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1511.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'Kremenets is the mountain in the Carpathians. It is one of the highest peaks of the Bukivski Verkhy. It is located in the northwestern part of Zakarpatska oblast to the northern west of village Stuzhytsya. The height of the mountain is 1221 m (according to other data — 1216 m).\nState borders of Poland, Slovakia and Ukraine meet on the top of Kremenets. Southeastern slopes of the mountain are on the territory of Ukraine (within the territory of the Uzhanskiy National Nature Park), northern slopes – on the territory of Poland and southwestern ones – Slovakia.  \nOne can start climbing the mountain from Ukrainian side from village Stuzhytsya. There is a frontier post in the village. Permission of border guards is needed. \n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(36,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Velykiy Berezniy','Stuzhytsya',49.02558517456055,22.60552406311035,'Dido-Dubâ (âGrandfather Oakâ)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0799.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1572.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1511.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'Two huge oaks that are unique monuments of nature grow in village Stuzhytsya – “Dido-Dub” (“Grandfather Oak”) and the Champion Oak. “Dido-Dub” is about 1100—1200 years old. The circumference of its trunk is 9.1 meters and its height is more than 30 meters. There are several legends about that tree. The Champion Oak has been found by the Head of the State Service of Reservation Service Hrynyk P.I. The tree is the oldest oak in Ukraine. It is about 1300 years old. The circumference of its trunk is 9.6 meters and its height is 30 meters. The Champion Oak has been declared as the National Tree of Ukraine as a result of Ukrainian National Competition in 2010.\nTourists who come to village Stuzhytsya always measure “Dido-Dub” by taking each other’s hand. 6-7 people are needed to embrace that huge tree.\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(37,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Velykiy Berezniy',NULL,48.92700958251953,22.667699813842773,'Mountain Krasiya',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/DSC_0095.jpg,img/markerImages/DSC_0116.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'   Krasiya is the skiing resort of Ukraine. It is 65 km remote from Uzhhorod and is located near villages Vyshka and Kostryno of Zakarpatska oblast.\nKrasiya has one of the longest alpine skiing tracks – about 3500 m. There are slopes for skiers of different training levels.\nThe season in Krasiya begins in December and ends in April. \n   Resort Krasiya was established in the Soviet Union times. There was the only one in Ukraine chair lift. The resort was actively built on in the eighties. During establishing of the resort it was taken into account that skiing tracks should be convenient, comfortable and universal – appropriate both for professionals and beginners.    \nAfter declaration of the independence of Ukraine new skiing tracks were established, modern skiing lifts installed and fan snow generators and retracks purchased.   \nAll skiing tracks in Krasiya are low grade, of medium and light difficulty levels, appropriate for beginners and professional skiers.  \nWidth of skiing tracks – from 100 to 350 m.\nLength of skiing tracks – from 300 m to 2500 m.\nLevel difference – from 80 to 300 m.\nTrack for sleighs.\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(38,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Velykiy Berezniy','Uzhok',48.988609313964844,22.821086883544922,'St. Archangel Michaelâs Church',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/DSC_0102.jpg,img/markerImages/7245.jpg,img/markerImages/2641.jpg,img/markerImages/2948.jpg,img/markerImages/3033.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'St. Archangel Michael’s Church is situated near the head of the river Uzh in small village Uzhok.\nThese are not only the perfect forms and proportions that impress you, but also the harmony of the structure and the surrounding landscape. Sometimes its tent roofs may resemble mountain peaks or the tops of the Carpathian spruces, and the other time they seem to be a fairy ship drawn by a magic power to the Carpathian highlands, ready to spread its sails and fly far away.\nAccording to the inscription on the doorpost, the temple was constructed in 1745 by Pavlo Toniv, a master from neighbouring village Bitlya and Ivan Tsyhanyn from village Tykhe. Other inscriptions say about the time of the major repairs.\nSt. Archangel Michael’s Church belongs to the temples of Boyko style. Boyko style churches are composed of three log sections crowned with three tops. The central top over the nave is always the predominant one. It is higher and bigger than the rest two ones and features the alteration of vertical and successively receding sloping sections in the roofs, creating a unique tiered effect. A small tent roof over the sanctuary and broach quadrangle tower over the babynets (narthex) are in admirable proportion.\nLike a shawl embracing the shoulders of the beloved one, the piddashshya (overhang) lies on the protruding parts of the corner joints. It protects the time-stained walls against often rains and at the same time it combines the three parts of the temple into a unique architectural composition.\nInside the church one will be fascinated by the carved iconostasis, a nice tabernacle and a canopy in the sanctuary.\nYou will feel great excitement watching the light and shade contrast when passing over to the grand and spacious nave from the half darkened narthex (common place for women).\nSt. Archangel Michael’s Church always greets all of its parishioners and admirers. It is the visiting card of the land.\n\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(39,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Velykiy Berezniy','Kostryno',48.94475555419922,22.581457138061523,'Wooden Church of the Intercession of the Holy Virgin',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'As researchers state the Church of the Intercession of the Holy Virgin was built in village Syanky, Turka district, Lvivska oblast in 1645. It was a classical Boyko church with three tops, the central being the predominant. In 1703 the church was taken to village Kostryno, Velykiy Berezniy district. \nThe framework tower, somewhat higher than the central tent roof, could be added over the narthex during the repairs of 1761. As a result of such reconstruction there appeared a raising of the forms from the east to the west, from altar part up to narthex, which helps us to understand the transferring of the Boyko style in church architecture to the Lemky style.\nThe open gallery at the top of the bell tower is a feature of the defensive towers of the past. \nThe biggest bell was requisitioned during the 1848-1849 Liberation War headed by Lajos Kossuth. \n  The Royal doors are fretted with rich carving. The lath on the gate is decorated with rosette and leaf flower motif. In the XVIII th century the animalistic motifs were often used in sacral carving of Zakarpattya. Thus, in the lower part of the doors we can see two chimerical dragons.\nFrom wherever you look at Kostryno temple you are charmed by its beauty and perfect proportions, by the almost ideal harmony of the structure and the landscape, and by the absolute and enigmatic lines of its silhouette. The Church of the Intercession of the Holy Virgin is certainly the outstanding monument of Ukrainian architecture. \n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(40,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Velykiy Berezniy','Sil',48.95309066772461,22.524246215820312,'Wooden Church of St. Basil the Great',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/2948.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/DSC_0072.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0016.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0799.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1572.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1511.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'   The  Church of St. Basil the Great in village Sol’, as the Kostryno church, was removed from  Galician village Syanky in 1707. The Lviv restorers consider the church to be built with three tops in Boyko style and transported together with the iconostasis to village Sol’ by four yokes of oxen. \nDuring the reconstruction of 1834 the church has lost its proportions and romantic mysteriousness of the Boyko church. It has got four sloped roof with a tiny tower over the altar. A bigger baroque tower rises over the entrance. \n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(41,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Velykiy Berezniy','Vyshka',48.94601821899414,22.67760467529297,'Wooden Church of St. Archangel Michael',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/DSC_0095.jpg,img/markerImages/DSC_0116.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'The church was built with three tops in Boyko style in 1700. In the second half of the XVIIIth century the tent roof over the narthex was substituted by framed bell tower higher than the central top.','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(42,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Velykiy Berezniy','Chornoholo',48.85255432128906,22.607736587524414,'St. Nicholas, the Miracle Worker',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0016.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0566.jpg,img/markerImages/teatralyna.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo_1.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo_3.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'There is a legend about the name of village Chornoholova. The saying goes that once upon a time there lived an opryshok (“Carpathian rebel”) Holovatiy, called so because of his big head. One day the count army surrounded his hut and set it on fire. When people came there they saw only a big burnt head. Since then the picturesque mountain village in Velykiy Berezniy district is called Chornoholova. \n Here, at the confluence of two mountain streams, as if having united the whole area, is located the marvelous church of St. Nicholas, the Miracle Worker.\nThe first thing that attracts attention is the solemn tower with the open arcade, a bit flattened cupola and a lantern. The overhang, supported by the carved posts, embraces the narthex and the nave of the temple. This is typical for Lemko architecture, so we can assume that originally in the 17th century, according to the age of spruce log sections, the temple looked otherwise. Doubly sloped roof that covers the altar part and somewhat wider nave, has most likely appeared after the reconstruction made by Matiy Khymych, a master from the village of Luchky, in 1794. The inscription on the door post proves that fact. The 18th century iconostasis composing of two parts is preserved in the nave. One passes to the church yard through the ancient wooden gates.\nIt is always calm and cosy near the church. The babble of the streams, the rustling of leaves, hip-hoppers’ chirring create the unearthly atmosphere of patriarchal peacefulness.\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(43,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Velykiy Berezniy','Bukivtsyovo',48.82412338256836,22.673120498657227,'Wooden Church of St. Anna ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/DSC_0095.jpg,img/markerImages/DSC_0116.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'The village of Bukivtsyovo is all surrounded by mountains from all sides. The St. Anna’ Church is located in the centre of the village on a rather high slope. At first you see the crosses and baroque tower lantern appearing in the trees, then they disappear while you cross the wooden bridge over the stream. And finally the beautiful architectural ensemble of a wooden entrance gate, a chapel and a church comes to view. The architects have chosen the perfect place for the church location as it looks like a majestic and fair queen with the Carpathians at her feet. And high trees together with winds continually beat bows before her. \nThe church was erected in the Boyko style. It was three sectional with three pyramid like tent roofs. For unknown reasons during the reconstruction of 1791 Hryhoriy Makarovych, a master, erected high framework tower with traditional baroque ending and the tent ceilings of the nave and altar part were hidden under the doubly sloped roof.\nHoused there are 18th century iconostasis, altar with tabernacle, an oblation table with an image of “Christ – the Grapevine”, altar cross, processional banners and wooden candlesticks.\nThe scenery is fascinating the whole year round. Summer gives all the shades of green. Autumn shows the contrast of gold resting nature with deep blue sky and red ripe apples. Winter charms with the eternal white silence broken by church bell ringing an','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(44,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Velykiy Berezniy','Sukhiy',48.946773529052734,22.791757583618164,'Wooden Church of St. John the Forerunner',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0799.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1572.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1511.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'The church was built in 1679 in Boyko style. Peculiar attention should be paid to ancient icons.','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(45,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Volovetskyi',NULL,48.510929107666016,23.5555144,'VERETSKYI PASS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0104_.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0206 (2).jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0036.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0353.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'Veretskyi pass, Voritskyi pass or Rusky Vorota is located on watershed of Striya and Latoritsa rivers.  The pass is 840 meters high above sea level. This place has an ancient history. It was a gate to Central Europe for many nomad formations: Scythians, Sarmats, Huns, Avars. Veretskyi pass, which geographically divides Transcarpthia and Lviv, has important place in history of Hungary. For many researchers opinion, Hungarian tribes leaded by Chieftain Arpad, passed exactly though Veretskyi pass to Danube plain and then settled between Tisza and Danube rivers in Pannonia.  \nIn the spring of 1241 year, Mongolian-Tatars troops leaded by khan Batyi burst though Rusky Vorota, overcome fortification and went to Nizhny Vorota. In the suburb of village Voyevoda Dionisiy of the small Rusin troop failed to stop the conquerors into Transcarpahia.\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(46,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Volovetskyi',NULL,48.81406021118164,23.169806,'Monument dedicated to Hungarians passing though Carpathians',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0016.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0566.jpg,img/markerImages/teatralyna.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo_1.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo_3.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'Historical sources says that in year of 888 Byzantine emperor Lev VI Mudriy invited Hungarians to take part in battle against Bulgarians, allowed them to moved from Ural and Volga region to Dakiya. In the years of 894-896 majority of Hungarian tribes leaded by Arpad, passed Carpathians, won battles against Bulgarians, and settled on Central Danube lowlands. \n\n Movement of Hungarians though Veretskyi pass confirmed by archeological researches of Hungarians entombment in Krilos village close to Halicha and city of Berehovo in Transcarpahia. \nExactly though Veretskyi pass the Hungarian tribes leaded by Chieftain Arpad passed and settled in Danube plain, and then settled between Tisza and Danube in Pannonia. Chronicler Nestor mentioned that it’s happened in year of 896. To commemorate this event, in Veretskyi pass a monument was mounted in year of 1896. At project of sculptor Peter Matla and architecture Arnold Medvedetskyi, the monument would have to have a form of chapel, which would consist with seven banks, which would symbolize seven Hungarian tribes. Inside should a sanctuary stone be installed made by granite, and in the upper bank an eagle bas-relief mounted as an ancient symbol of Hungarians.\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(47,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Volovetskyi','Huklyve',48.709626,23.247021,'Ð¡hurch of St. Spirit',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/DSC_0095.jpg,img/markerImages/DSC_0116.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'The church without any hyperborbilization is one of the most prominent highlands masterpieces’. The plane of the roof is covered by fir shingle that plays by different coloures under the sun. The church is well-proportionated and nice. Each element complements one another. The columns are mastery designed; the doorpost has a carving, the baroque towel is one of perfect among similar ones.  \nThe temple is built in XVIII century by fir. In the Soviet time, the church serves an atheism museum that gives possibility to preserve it from plundering and dull alternation.                                                                                               \n     The iconostasis of the year of 1784 is also preserved, that is a valuable monument of carving and paint. Within carving prevails baroque and rococo elements. Among other icons differs portrayal of “Virgin of Odihirtiyi». The unique for Transcarpathia is a composition of “Baptism of Rus’ by St. Volodimir”.\nAccording to historical notes, the author of the icons was a German national - France Peer.\nNear to the entrance of the church two wooden crosses are preserved. On the right side near to the entrance, two-tier bell-towel is found.    \n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(48,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Volovetskyi','Zhdeniyevo',48.773869,22.971161,'Zhdeniyevo',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/DSC_0095.jpg,img/markerImages/DSC_0116.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'are situated.\nIn one of those houses imperceptibly a girl growth up under name of Eva. She was tall like a fir, and beautiful like early dew. Everyone’s heart sank who met her.\nHer beauty forced to beat one heart faster and faster. Then cheeks turn to red and proud eagle gaze turn to grow dim. Everything around disappeared and just two – young man and girl were only in the whole world. They understood each other by look, gesture, breath.\nThe parents were happy of that couple and prepared for wedding. However, unexpected news suddenly broke the happiness: an evil was attached the land. Everyone who was able to hold arms went to battle.\nMen began prepare themselves for far road. On the roadside, next to a large oak the young man and girl were standing in each other embraces. Silently swear to love each other forever. The young man took a sharp knife and carves on the trunk words: «Zhdi nya Evo», which literally means, (“Wait me Eva”).\nThe time were passing, the tree on the roadside growth, and like a memory about passionate love, on its truck growth and growth the words «ZHDENIYEVO».\nOnce a state lord visited the land and saw the inscription on the tree and supposed that this is a name of the village, and wrote down in his papers - “Zhdeniyevo village”.\nThus, the most beautiful human feeling gives name to the mountain village. \n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(49,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Mizhhirya','Synevyr',48.575699,23.686813,'National park âSynevyrâ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/DSC_0095.jpg,img/markerImages/DSC_0116.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'National Park \"Synevyr\" is a leading environmental research institution provides protection, preservation and study of unique corner of the Carpathians - Tereblyanska upper valley of Transcarpathia.\nNational Park \"Synevyr\" was created in 1989 to preserve, restor and mailntain economical usage of natural resources, systems and facilities that having particular scientific and aesthetic values within different latitudinal zones southwestern macroslopes of Gorgan. Therefore, a special task of the NP \"Synevyr\" as protected structures is preservation of natural, historical and cultural complexes and objects, creating conditions for organized tourism, recreation and other outdoor activities in natural conditions in compliance with the regime of natural systems and their changes in recreational usage, the development of scientific advice on environmental protection issue and careful usage of natural resources, environmental and educational work and so on. \n\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(50,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Mizhhirya','Synevyr',48.617009,23.683988,'Synevyr lake',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/DSC_0102.jpg,img/markerImages/7245.jpg,img/markerImages/2641.jpg,img/markerImages/2948.jpg,img/markerImages/3033.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'Lake Synevyr rightly considered the most precious natural treasure of the national park. It is the largest natural lake in the Ukrainian Carpathians, one of the seven natural wonders of Ukraine. It lies between the mountains, among the spruce-fir forest at an altitude of 989 meters above sea level, near the village of Synevyrska Polyana. It been formed though collapse of the rocks that blocked the valley of a mountain stream. This happened about 10-11 thousand years ago, and now we have the opportunity to admire the unique beauty of the reservoir.\nThe average area of the lake Synevyr is 4.5 - 7.5 ha, depth is from 8 to 23.5 m.\nThere are several species of trout found - brook, lake, rainbow. This is another proof that the water is very clean.\nLake recognized wetland of international importance and was included in the list of so-called Ramsar sites (Ramsar Convention).\nLandscapes around the water surface is surprisingly grand and picturesque. Steep slopes are covered with fir trees, whose age reaches of 140-160 years. Middle surface of the water like a blue iris of the eye, is a small island. Because of this, the Synevyr lake is called the Marine eye.\nThere is a legend about Synevyr exists where the picturesque lake created by the flow of tears of count\'s daughter Syn, on the place where her lover, who was a simple shepherd of Verkhovyna Vyr, was killed by stone block by order of the graph.\nInteresting fact: At the floor of the lake Synevyr there is a hole that serves as a natural regulator of the water level and thus cannot overflows its banks, even during big floods.\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(51,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Mizhhirya',NULL,48.52661,23.696724,'Reabilitation center of brown bear',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'The population of brown bears in Ukraine is about 300 species. There are a number of these animals that are kept in captivity. In some cases, these bears kept in poor conditions or their retantion  violates the environmental legislations. Thus, a formation of a specialized rehabilitation center of brown bears was established.\nThe purpose of the center of brown bear is rehabilitation of individuals who have experienced abuse, victimіs of natural disasters, retention of confiscated animals, reproduction of their natural populations, temporary overexposure of animals stoped at the border due to violations of environmental legislation, etc.\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(52,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Mizhhirya',NULL,48.391441,23.655879,'Museum of forest and rafting',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/2948.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/DSC_0072.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0016.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0799.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1572.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1511.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'The museum of forest and rafting offers possibility to get acquaintance with models of components, structures and devices of all process harvesting, sorting, storage and transportation of wood in the form of rafts. In an accessible, clearly form visitors can find information about the history, the lives of our ancestors, their hard work, plight destinity of their families. There is also a variety of axes, saws, used in different parts of harvesting and processing of timber. There is everything might be found from the costume and tools to layout hut (temporary houses of woodcutters), which are exhibits of the museum.\nLife and customs of  highlanders quite unique and interesting, unfortunately, has little forgotten, but things revive in the imagination when you get acquainted with the goods, kitchenware and all sorts of utensils made from wood.\nVarious cans, konovtsi, heletky, barrels, bowls are only small part of the exhibition, which is striking in its originality, beauty, form, method of manufacture. Equally interesting locals shoes: leather and rubber sandals, mens leather topanky with a wooden sole in high heels, vintage bochkory that carved from solid wood.\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(53,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Mizhhirya','Pylypec',48.658428,23.323753,'Waterfall Shypit',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/DSC_0095.jpg,img/markerImages/DSC_0116.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'Waterfall Shypit is one of the most beautiful and flowing waterfalls in Transcarpathia. It is located on the suburb of the Pylypec village and has convenient accessibility, which is very important for visitors to be able to admire its beauty. Water flowing from the valleys Borzhava breaking up on huge boulders forming spectacular waterfalls, clouds of water dust and loud roar. The waterfall got its name because of the noise of falling water. His loud voice from far is heard like a whisper. The greatest power the waterfall has in spring when the snow is melting and in autumn when there a lot of precipitation. However, in other seasons of the year, its beauty and power will amaze you because of falling water high is fourteen meters. It should be noticed that since 1993 during celebration of Kupala holidays hippies and other members of non-formal groups are coming here from Ukraine and all over of Europe.','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(54,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Mizhhirya','Pylypec',48.669971,23.340528,'Church of the Nativity of the Blessed Virgin',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0016.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0566.jpg,img/markerImages/teatralyna.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo_1.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo_3.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'Pylypets village is located in the valley of the river Repynky. On the shore of sparkling stream we face the Church of the Nativity of the Blessed Virgin. Situated along the path surrounded by trees, as a symbol of faight it strictl and confidently keeps calm and peace of the village.\nAccording to Michael Syrokhman statement the church was built from 1759 to 1762.\nInside an iconostasis of the XVIII century preserved.\nNear the temple is a wooden two-tiered bell tower found, built probably in 1758.\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(55,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Mizhhirya','Kolochava',48.431593,23.725382,'Wooden church of the Holy Spirit',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/DSC_0095.jpg,img/markerImages/DSC_0116.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'In Kolochava, in a small hill, near to the main road a wooden church of the Holy Spirit is situated, that belongs to the highest architectural achievements of Transcarpathia. According to the inscription on the door-post it says: \"This church is created in this house in 1795 by pastor Ioana Popovich, under king of Frantsyshki II and by master Ferenc Tekke.  Then it was a great hunger\". In ancient times, hunger is often accompanied the people life in mountains, and sometimes it was recorded in parohialnyh books, but in Kolochava it was recorded in the door-post of the church.\n   The church was closed for a long time and called a  \"the museum of atheism,\" from outside it remained intact in its original glory, even it was completely devastated inside.\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(56,2,'Украина','Ukraine','Закарпатська область','Ужгородський район','Ужгород',48.587491479026504,22.310651335937564,'TEst NEWS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/DSC_0102.jpg,img/markerImages/7245.jpg,img/markerImages/2641.jpg,img/markerImages/2948.jpg,img/markerImages/3033.jpg','info','','admin','28.04.2015',0,'<p>Testing NEWS 1234 )</p>\r\n','','','','','','','','','','2',1,NULL,NULL),(57,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Mizhhirya','Izki',48.650841,23.364947,'The St. Nicholas church',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/2948.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/DSC_0072.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0016.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0799.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1572.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1511.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'The St. Nicholas church was built early ХVIII century. Today the church is a classic example of \"Verkhovynsky Baroque\". Inside the temple a great icon of the Virgin remains, art critic of Gregory Logvyn calls that «Carpathian Madonna».','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(58,2,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','Mizhhirya','Kolochava',48.435849,23.738855,'âOld villageâ museum',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',0,'\"Old Village\" is the first rural museum of architecture in Transcarpathia. It is located between the blue waves of the river Kolochavky and evergreen array Chertezhyka.\nSkansen is the fourth museum created within the project of \"Kolochava a village of ten museums\". The museum recreated a village of ancient Verhoviny by kolochava exhibits that provide  with 300-year history about life style of local residents. At Skansen is represents cultural monuments of different periods and different groups of people and their type of activity.\nToday the Museum \"Old village\" consist of nearly twenty buildings and ancillary outbuildings.\nThe purpose of Kolchava museum is to save distinctive history of the village and attract tourists. Since 2008, the museum of Kolochava has been included to Sinevyr tourist route. Today there are museums, \"Old Village\", \"Soviet school\", \"Czech School\", museum of the famous Czech writer Ivan Olbracht,  museum of baroque folk architecture of 1795 - a wooden church of the Holy Spirit, the museum \"Kolochavska narrow gauge\", \"Bunker of Shtayer\", memorial of “Warriors- internationalists” and Museum \"Arpad line\". There other projects for new museums are being developed.\n  It is also planned to restore the smithy, the tavern, the mill, and rebuild the church of 1580 that once existed in Kolochava and to create an amphitheater for 500 spectators.\n','','','','','','','','','',NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(60,0,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Creation of cross-border tourism network mechanism',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0799.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1572.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1511.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',1,'<p><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">The mechanism is based on the most resent experience of the neighboring countries on tourism and recreation development as well as partnership in the tourism industry building up and developing. The best experts on tourism from Hungary, Slovakia, Romania and Ukraine have been involved in the mechanism elaboration.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">The Network Concept is aimed at establishing a platform for regional tourist products promotion in accordance with the purposes and tasks of domestic and inbound tourism. Concept of cross-border tourism network of HU-SK-RO-UA region presents different views on the main principals and ways how the tourism actors can be united to form effective integration and co-operation in the region.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">The <strong>CTN “Carpathian Tourist road</strong>” is a public initiative that brings network’s participants together on the basis of co-operation agreement; it estimates and guarantees the quality, originality, uniqueness of creation, partnership, communication and promotion of joint tourist products created by the travel agencies of HU-RO-SK-UA cross-border region.</span></p><p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>The main advantages of participation in CTN «Carpathian Tourist Road»:</strong></span></p><ol><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">Increase the competitiveness of CTN «Carpathian Tourist Road»participants at domestic and international tourist markets.</span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">Creation of CTN «Carpathian Tourist Road» in frames of the project “Carpathian tourist road-2” supported and financed by the European Union.</span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">Participation in the formation of CTN «Carpathian Tourist Road» operation principles.</span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">Creation of joint tourist product and development new markets for consumers.</span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">Sales of tourist routs and packages, use an international system of positioning, promotion and marketing of tourist products under the brand “CTR” («Carpathian Tourist Road»).</span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">Preparation and conduction of training programs for the network participants and development of the mechanism of increase the region tourist attractiveness.</span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">Participation in tourist cross-border events (festivals, exhibitions, fairs).</span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">Presence on the web-portal www.carpathianroad.com by placing the information and products promotion on it.</span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">Collection, processing and dissemination information about HU -SK-RO -UA cross-border regions of the neighbouring countries. Development and dissemination of a joint promotional products.</span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">Participation in lengthening European tourist routes to Ukraine and connecting the tourist routs network in Carpathian region.</span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">Visualization of tourist attractions (interactive and paper maps, tourist routs certificates, etc.). Adaptation of CTR to the European system of tourist routs.</span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">Receiving consultations on legal, business and management issues.</span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">Access to the results of research on the state of tourist market.</span></li><li><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">Support by national and regional authorities in terms of decision making and mechanisms of its implementation.</span></li></ol><p><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">&nbsp;<img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" alt=\"promomaterials\" src=\"/img/content/DSC_0007.jpg\" height=\"594\" width=\"804\" /></span></p>','','','','','','','','','',NULL,0,NULL,NULL),(62,0,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'First International Training on development of cross-border tourism network “Carpathian Tourist Road”',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/DSC_0095.jpg,img/markerImages/DSC_0116.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',1,'\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\"><strong> The network is </strong>is a non-government initiative that joins together participants on the base of cooperation agreements, defines and guarantees the quality, originality, uniqueness of creation, partnership, communication and promotion of joint tourist products of HU-SK-RO-UA region.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">More than 50 participants took part in the event. Among them were delegations from Slovak Republic, Hungary, Czech Republic and other regions of Ukraine as well as representatives of regional and district organizations and institutions of Zakarpattia region that engaged in tourism.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">The training took place in the frame of the project&nbsp;<strong>“Carpathian tourist road 2”</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong>that&nbsp; is implementing in the frame of the&nbsp; Hungary-Slovakia-Romania-Ukraine ENPI CBC Programme 2007-2013 by the communal enterprise “Agency of regional development and cross-border co-operation “Transcarpathia” of Zakarpattya oblast council”,&nbsp; Agency for the Support of Regional Development Košice and East Slovak Museum in Košice. &nbsp;Grant contract № HUSKROUA/1001/013, 07.06.2012.</span></p>','','','','','','','','','',NULL,0,NULL,NULL),(64,0,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'XIIIth International Fair and Exhibition “Toureurocenter-Transcarpathia 2014”',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0016.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0566.jpg,img/markerImages/teatralyna.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo_1.jpg,img/markerImages/beregovo_3.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',1,'\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">All rayons of Zakarpattia oblast and 8 regions of Ukraine, namely, Volyn, Zaporizhia, Ivano-Frankivsk, Kyiv, Ternopil, Odesa, Kherson and Cherkasy region presented their tourism potential and their tour products. There were some European countries, namely, Hungary and Slovakia.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;\">ARD «Transcarpathia» together with partners, Agency for the Support of Regional Development Košice and East Slovak Museum in Košice, presented the project “Carpathian Tourist Road” and its activities, namely, a regular “Carpathian Tourist Road” in the tourism magazine “Unikum”, mechanism of cross-border tourism network, cross-border tourism products, etc.</span></p>','','','','','','','','','',NULL,0,NULL,NULL),(66,0,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia','','',48.62422063319235,22.294424084655702,'Project for support economy of Zakarpatska oblast','','','','','','','','','img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/DSC_0072.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0016.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0799.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1572.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1511.jpg','info','','admin','28.04.2015',1,'<p style=\"text-align:justify\">This project aims to improve the level of economic development in Zakarpattia oblast by means of enhancement of tourism promotion and its improvement. This will be achieved through the support and development of local tourist products and services by means of intensive development of regional tourist infrastructure, introduction of innovative tools for tourism development by improvement of tourism sector promotion in the region, as well as development and implementation if the effective regional policy in the field of tourism.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The project will create the basis for effective communication between tourists that visit Zakarpattia oblast and providers of various services and products in the tourism sector, as well as for improvement of the tourist image of Zakarpattia oblast by means of carrying out of promotional campaign for project activities, attraction of additional investments for local tourism infrastructure development. This will facilitate the development of new tourist products in the region and increase of the employment in the region due to the need to provide services to a larger number of international and domestic tourists in a larger number of tourist facilities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The following specific results are expected to be met within the action activities implementation:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>An extended network of tourist infrastructure facilities in the region;</li>\r\n	<li>Increased awareness of the region&rsquo;s visitors about its tourism potential through the Internet resources;</li>\r\n	<li>Increased the number of highly-qualified large scaled events of tourism promotion;</li>\r\n	<li>Created theoretical background of the tourism infrastructure development and management for representatives of raion administrations, tourism actors and agencies of local development;</li>\r\n	<li>Systematization and equipping of tourist routes network in the region.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Promotion of tourism is of a high importance in the project&rsquo;s implementation, as the project provides for the development of new online resources in the tourism sphere (Internet portal www.carpathianroad.com), elaboration and printing of manuals, creation of videos on tourism promotion, etc. The mentioned Internet portal is a strong tourism promotional tool within Ukraine and abroad for spreading quality information among domestic and foreign tourists. It will stand out for its innovative mechanisms and practical use. There will be: visualization of tourist attractions by help of pictures, spherical panoramas and informational video film, electronic topographic map with tourist routes network, GPS coordinates of the main points as well as the characteristic of the routes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A number of trainings will be carried out as well for representatives of local authorities and tourist market actors on tourist infrastructure development and management in the region, increase of the service level in the tourism sector.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">And that&rsquo;s just some of the activities that will be implemented within the project. Therefore, the target group of the project is really significant: regional communities, local associations for tourism development in the region, tourism actors, teachers and students of tourism departments and faculties, youths, and disabled tourists.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">We invite the residents and visitors of Zakarpattia to support the initiative of tourism development in our region.</p>\r\n','<p style=\"text-align:justify\">This project aims to improve the level of economic development in Zakarpattia oblast by means of enhancement of tourism promotion and its improvement. This will be achieved through the support and development of local tourist products and services by means of intensive development of regional tourist infrastructure, introduction of innovative tools for tourism development by improvement of tourism sector promotion in the region, as well as development and implementation if the effective regional policy in the field of tourism.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The project will create the basis for effective communication between tourists that visit Zakarpattia oblast and providers of various services and products in the tourism sector, as well as for improvement of the tourist image of Zakarpattia oblast by means of carrying out of promotional campaign for project activities, attraction of additional investments for local tourism infrastructure development. This will facilitate the development of new tourist products in the region and increase of the employment in the region due to the need to provide services to a larger number of international and domestic tourists in a larger number of tourist facilities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The following specific results are expected to be met within the action activities implementation:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>An extended network of tourist infrastructure facilities in the region;</li>\r\n	<li>Increased awareness of the region&rsquo;s visitors about its tourism potential through the Internet resources;</li>\r\n	<li>Increased the number of highly-qualified large scaled events of tourism promotion;</li>\r\n	<li>Created theoretical background of the tourism infrastructure development and management for representatives of raion administrations, tourism actors and agencies of local development;</li>\r\n	<li>Systematization and equipping of tourist routes network in the region.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Promotion of tourism is of a high importance in the project&rsquo;s implementation, as the project provides for the development of new online resources in the tourism sphere (Internet portal www.carpathianroad.com), elaboration and printing of manuals, creation of videos on tourism promotion, etc. The mentioned Internet portal is a strong tourism promotional tool within Ukraine and abroad for spreading quality information among domestic and foreign tourists. It will stand out for its innovative mechanisms and practical use. There will be: visualization of tourist attractions by help of pictures, spherical panoramas and informational video film, electronic topographic map with tourist routes network, GPS coordinates of the main points as well as the characteristic of the routes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A number of trainings will be carried out as well for representatives of local authorities and tourist market actors on tourist infrastructure development and management in the region, increase of the service level in the tourism sector.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">And that&rsquo;s just some of the activities that will be implemented within the project. Therefore, the target group of the project is really significant: regional communities, local associations for tourism development in the region, tourism actors, teachers and students of tourism departments and faculties, youths, and disabled tourists.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">We invite the residents and visitors of Zakarpattia to support the initiative of tourism development in our region.</p>\r\n','','','','','','','','','4',0,'img/content/NEWS/NEWS/ava.jpg',NULL),(68,0,'null','Ukraine','null','null','null',0,0,'UNICUM. UNIQUE TRANSCARPATHIA',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0104_.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0206 (2).jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0036.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0353.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0104_.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0206 (2).jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0036.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0353.jpg','info','','admin','28.04.2015',1,'<p>The periodical is available at print press distribution points, as well as at exhibitions and other events, planed within the project implementation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://arr.com.ua/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/DSC_0104.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://arr.com.ua/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/DSC_0104-1024x682.jpg\" style=\"border-style:solid; border-width:2px; height:533px; margin:2px; width:800px\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://arr.com.ua/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/DSC_0112.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://arr.com.ua/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/DSC_0112-1024x682.jpg\" style=\"border-style:solid; border-width:2px; height:533px; margin:2px; width:800px\" /></a></p>\r\n','','','','','','','','','','2',0,NULL,NULL),(70,1,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'ARD “Transcarpathia” organizes training on tourism development of Zakarpattia oblast',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0799.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1572.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1511.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',1,'\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>The purpose of the training</strong> – defining the mechanism for implementing of cross-border tourist network “Carpathian tourist road” on the territory of Zakarpattia oblast.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">The target audience of the training: active tourism actors of Zakarpattia oblast, agencies of regional development, representatives of tourist &nbsp;information centers and representatives of authorities.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">For reference:</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">The training takes place in the frame of the project <strong>“Carpathian tourist road 2” </strong>that &nbsp;is being implemented &nbsp;in the frame of the&nbsp; Hungary-Slovakia-Romania-Ukraine ENPI CBC Programme 2007-2013 by the communal enterprise “Agency of regional development and cross-border cooperation “Transcarpathia” of Zakarpattya oblast council”,&nbsp; Agency for the Support of Regional Development Košice and East Slovak Museum in Košice. &nbsp;Grant contract № HUSKROUA/1001/013, 07.06.2012.</span></p>','','','','','','','','','',NULL,0,NULL,NULL),(72,1,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Starting Conference of the project “Support to the economy of Zakarpattia oblast through its tourism capacity development and promotion”',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/DSC_0095.jpg,img/markerImages/DSC_0116.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',1,'\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" data-canvas-width=\"113.08639999999998\" data-angle=\"0\" data-font-name=\"g_font_3\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"> The purpose of the Starting conference – presentation of the objectives, activities and expected results of the Project, as well as informing the public about the launch of a new investment project in the field of tourism. The project “Support to the economy of Zakarpattia oblast through its tourism capacity development and promotion” financed by the European Union within the program “Support to regional development in Ukraine”, Grant agreement #2014/343-149 of 24.07.2014. The project is</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" data-canvas-width=\"208.2511999999999\" data-angle=\"0\" data-font-name=\"g_font_3\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">being implemented by Zakarpattia oblast council in partnership with the Communal enterprise “Agency of regional development and cross-border cooperation “Transcarpathia” of Zakarpattia regional council”. The total project budget is 890,554.00 euro, of which the amount of EU co-financing: 712,443.00 euro.</span></div>\r\n<div data-canvas-width=\"278.3184\" data-angle=\"0\" data-font-name=\"g_font_7\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div data-canvas-width=\"278.3184\" data-angle=\"0\" data-font-name=\"g_font_7\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Specific objectives of the project are:</span></div>\r\n<div data-canvas-width=\"111.9824\" data-angle=\"0\" data-font-name=\"g_font_3\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">1. Support and development of local tourist products and services through improvement of regional tourism infrastructure.</span></div>\r\n<div data-canvas-width=\"54.59279999999999\" data-angle=\"0\" data-font-name=\"g_font_3\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">2. Introduction of innovative tools for tourism development through improvement of tourism promotion in the oblast.</span></div>\r\n<div data-canvas-width=\"285.4208\" data-angle=\"0\" data-font-name=\"g_font_9\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">3. Development and introduction of effective regional policy in the tourism field through improvement of the tourist routes management mechanism.</span></div>\r\n<div data-canvas-width=\"285.4208\" data-angle=\"0\" data-font-name=\"g_font_9\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div data-canvas-width=\"285.4208\" data-angle=\"0\" data-font-name=\"g_font_9\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">For more information, please, contact:</span></div>\r\n<div data-canvas-width=\"127.6224\" data-angle=\"0\" data-font-name=\"g_font_3\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>Tetyana Galishyn</strong></span></div>\r\n<div data-canvas-width=\"242.3096\" data-angle=\"0\" data-font-name=\"g_font_3\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">PR and communication manager</span></div>\r\n<div data-canvas-width=\"174.2296\" data-angle=\"0\" data-font-name=\"g_font_6\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Communal enterprise “Agency of regional development and cross-border cooperation “</span></div>\r\n<div data-canvas-width=\"214.08399999999995\" data-angle=\"0\" data-font-name=\"g_font_6\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Transcarpathia” of Zakarpattia regional council”</span></div>\r\n<div data-canvas-width=\"18.799933333333332\" data-angle=\"0\" data-font-name=\"g_font_3\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Тел.: +38 (050) 707-98-78</span></div>','','','','','','','','','',NULL,0,NULL,NULL),(74,1,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Transcarpathia',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Final conference of \"Carpathian tourist road 2\" project',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/2948.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/DSC_0072.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0016.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0256.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_0799.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1572.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1511.jpg',NULL,NULL,'admin','28.04.2015',1,'\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The project has been implemented by the Communal enterprises “Agency of Regional Development and Cross-border co-operation “Transcarpathia” Zakarpattya Oblast Council”, Agency for Support of Regional Development Kosice and East Slovak Museum.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The project is focused on strengthening the position of Carpathian region in European tourism sector by means of harmonization the process of tourism development at the local/regional and cross-border levels and increasing the level of competitiveness of the Carpathian tourism industry in the EU market.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The conference aims </strong>to make final wrap-up of the project realization, highlight the project outputs including presentation of organizational model of tourism development and mechanism of cross-border cooperation “Carpathian Tourist Road” based on experts recommendations, international experience and training participants, presentation of the experience of European countries in marketing and coordination of tourism industry at the regional level and strategic approach of its development.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The event is supported by Zakarpattya Oblast Council and Transcarpathian Regional State Administration.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Main conference organizer is Communal enterprises “Agency of Regional Development and Cross-border co-operation “Transcarpathia” Zakarpattya Oblast Council”.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Representatives of regional and local authorities engaged in tourism development, tourism enterprises, organizations and experts from neighboring countries and other regions of Ukraine as well as rayons of Zakarpattia oblast are planned to be invited to the event.</p>','','','','','','','','','',NULL,0,NULL,NULL),(78,3,'','Ukraine','','','',0,0,'About ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/markerImages/IMG_0799.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1317.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_9438.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1572.jpg,img/markerImages/IMG_1511.jpg','info','','admin','28.04.2015',1,'<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Producers (travel agencies, sector associations)</strong>will gain surplus benefits by providing a common marketing strategy aimed to promote and use the Carpathian Tourist Road brand; they will also be able to widen and deepen their business relations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;As well as<strong> distributors (travel agencies and agents)</strong> and l<strong>ocal key participants (governmental and non-governmental institutions, mass media, business units). </strong>They will benefit from promotion of the region indirectly, because the target area is going to be better advertised by the cross-border network and the tourist products of the target region will be promoted successfully abroad.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;That way, the CTN &ldquo;Carpathian Tourist Road&rdquo; will increase the competitiveness of 4 countries and their products.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;The Hu-SK-RO-UA experts&rsquo; survey shows that a basis for tourism development at the regional level is the following key factors: developed tourism infrastructure, tourism products and events attractive for tourists carried out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;The main tool for products and services promotion within the HU-SK-RO-UA cross-border region is an Internet platform. There are number of Internet portals in every region which include a lot of information on the tourist destinations of cross-border territory and inform about activities of tourism actors, but all the portals are written mostly in the national languages and in one foreign language at maximum</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;It is appropriate to establish the CTN Carpathian Tourist Road of HU-SK-RO-UA region at this stage as well as to elaborate a Carpathian Tourist Road Brand aimed at uniting HU-SK-RO-UA countries together by geographical principal; that will make it easier to recognize the brand and will give better possibilities for promoting of the brand on domestic and foreign tourism markets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;The CTN &ldquo;Carpathian Tourist Road&rdquo; might become an initiator and leader that will be able to elaborate and promote the cross-border tourist routes involving the unique nature, history and culture heritage which make them attractive for Ukrainian and foreign tourists.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;Aimed to attract more people to the region and introduce the tourism destinations of HU-RO-SK-UA cross-border region among the proposed activities the tourism routes can be classified by topic, duration or destination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;Special role and attention is given to the communication policy of CTN &ldquo;Carpathian Tourist Road&rdquo; as a system of correlations between the Network and potential consumers in order to make the last to buy a tourism product. The Internet page <a href=\"http://carpathianroad.com\">http://carpathianroad.com</a> plays a key role in communication policy. It is a platform for spreading the information/news about its activities, database of enterprises and organizations that are participants to the network and database of products and services of the network&rsquo;s participants, etc. testesteste</p>\r\n','','','','','','','','','','1',0,NULL,NULL),(79,0,'Україна','Ukraine','Закарпатська область','Іршавський район','Ужгород',48.64016871811908,22.313232421875,'Test NEWS',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','info','','admin','28.04.2015',0,'<p>Test NEWS</p>\r\n','<p>тестова Новина</p>\r\n','','','','','','','','','2',1,NULL,NULL),(80,2,'Украина','Ukraine','Закарпатська область','null','Ужгород',48.62332665309278,22.29915576190183,'Tasting room Shardone','','','','','','','','','','tasting_hall','tasting_room','admin','28.04.2015',0,'<p>Shardone is the first Uzhhorod tasting room. It has been selected due to following reasons:&nbsp;<br />\r\n- is one of the most popular and the most attended tourist objects in Uzhhorod;&nbsp;<br />\r\n- has very convenient location: in ancient part of the town, in pedestrian zone; and<br />\r\n- is a standard of wine-making traditions and cultivated taste.&nbsp;<br />\r\nIt is said in legends that representatives of Uzhhorod noble families gathered in that cellar together and discussed different issues with foreign ambassadors when drinking good wines.&nbsp;</p>\r\n','<p>Шардоне - перший ужгородський дегустаційний зал. Обраний з кількох причин:&nbsp;<br />\r\n- є одним із найпопулярніших і найбільш відвідуваних туристичних об&rsquo;єктів Ужгорода;&nbsp;<br />\r\n- має надзвичайно вдале розташування: у старовинній частині міста, в пішохідній туристичній зоні;<br />\r\n- є еталоном виноробних традицій та вишуканого смаку.<br />\r\nЛегенди твердять, що саме в цьому підвалі у давні часи збиралися ужгородські вельможі і за келихом доброго вина вели дружні бесіди із заморськими послами.&nbsp;</p>\r\n','','','','','','','','','3',1,NULL,NULL),(81,0,'Украина','Ukraine','Вінницька область','Тульчинський район','',48.69096039092549,28.76220703125,'Test',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','info','','editor','28.04.2015',0,'<p>1234</p>\r\n','<p>1234</p>\r\n','<p>1234</p>\r\n','','','','','','','','2',1,NULL,NULL),(82,1,'Украина','Ukraine','Львівська область','','Львів',49.816720843571765,24.0655517578125,'Test 1234',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/content/DSC_0007.jpg','info','','admin','28.04.2015',0,'<p>2134</p>\r\n','<p>124124</p>\r\n','<p>124124124</p>\r\n','<p>12414124</p>\r\n','','','','','','','2',1,NULL,NULL),(83,0,'','Ukraine','','','',0,0,'test2',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','','editor','28.04.2015',0,'<p>23</p>\r\n','','','','','','','','','','2',1,NULL,NULL),(84,0,'Украина','Poland','Київська область','Кагарлицький район','Стави',49.89463439573421,30.60791015625,'Test marker',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'img/content/01-4.jpg','militaries,gardens,fishing','rock_climbing,ski_and_freeride,active_rest:','editor','28.04.2015',0,'<pre>\r\n<code><strong>public</strong>&nbsp;<strong>boolean</strong>&nbsp;equals(Object&nbsp;obj)&nbsp;{&nbsp;\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>return</strong>&nbsp;(<strong>this</strong>&nbsp;==&nbsp;obj);&nbsp;\r\n}&nbsp;</code></pre>\r\n','','','','','','','','','','5',1,NULL,NULL),(85,0,'Ukraine','Ukraine','Zhytomyrs\'ka oblast','Lyubars\'kyi district','',49.80206863564959,27.90893465280533,'